        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 9:17PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 917 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
St. Anne, or 8 miles south of Momence, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hopkins Park and St. Anne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
